“Last year Daifuku was superb! So how do you elevate into Daifuku 2.0?”

Here is the menu 😊
1. Baileys Caramel 百利甜酒
Baileys mousse, salted caramel truffle encased in chocolate choux, covered in coffee mochi.

2. Coconut Calamansi 椰子和酸柑
Light coconut mousse, calamansi ganache truffle, almond praline, vanilla sponge in yellow mochi 

3. Raspberry Lychee 覆盆子和荔枝
Raspberry mousse, lychee martini truffle, raspberry confit, vanilla sponge in pink mochi.

4. Chocolate Blackcurrant 黑醋栗
Chocolate mousse, layers of blackberry and blackcurrant ganache, salted caramel ganache truffle, chocolate sponge in violet mochi.

5. Jasmine Grenadine 茉莉花茶
Jasmine milk tea mousse, grenadine confit, vanilla sponge in jasmine mochi. 

6. Matcha Mascarpone 日本抹茶
Soft matcha mousse, homemade anko tsubuan, mascarpone cheese cream encased in matcha choux pastry in matcha mochi skin.

I really hope you enjoy them as much as we do, by the way, are you sure you want to share?? 😄😄

My experience with @quadra.surface for my new kitchen.
I know Quadra from @sidhartaarchitect and with his recommendation, I choose Pietra Grigio for my kitchen.

And the result?

They are absolutely beautiful.

A flower cake can be a lovely and thoughtful gift to give to a friend for a special occasion or just to show appreciation. Here are some steps to help you make a flower cake for your friend:

1. Bake the cake: You can use your friend's favorite cake recipe or try something new. You'll need to make two or three round cakes of different sizes to stack on top of each other.

2. Prepare the frosting: You can use buttercream or cream frosting, which are both great options for decorating. You can also add food coloring to create different colors.

3. Crumb coat: Apply a thin layer of frosting all over the cake to seal in the crumbs. Let it chill in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.

4. Decorate with flowers: Use flower-shaped buttercream decorations to create a floral design on the cake. You can arrange the flowers in a wreath pattern, or create a cascade of flowers down the side of the cake. Be creative and have fun with it!

5. Add finishing touches: Once you've decorated the cake with flowers, you can add some final touches such as edible glitter or pearls.

6. Present your flower cake to your friend: Place your flower cake on a cake stand or platter and present it to your friend. Be sure to take a photo before you cut into it to show off your beautiful creation!

Remember to personalize your flower cake to your friend's tastes and preferences. You can add their favorite flavors, colors, and decorations to make it extra special for them.
